WEBVTT

00:03.045 --> 00:05.172
NARRA TOR:
Previously on Heroes.

00:07.091 --> 00:09.002
What happened?
You tried to
kill yourself.

00:09.093 --> 00:11.209
Ijumped and you flew up
and you caught me.

00:11.304 --> 00:14.842
You jumped 25 feet to
a fire escape. I climbed up
and carried you down.

00:16.809 --> 00:17.798
You understand?

00:19.437 --> 00:22.474
lspoke
to a very nice woman
at the adoption agency.

00:22.565 --> 00:25.523
She said they were going
to try to get in touch
with your birth parents.

00:26.277 --> 00:28.814
But you can't
protect me forever.

00:28.905 --> 00:31.317
I know, and
it breaks my heart.

00:31.407 --> 00:32.772
I love you, Dad.

00:37.330 --> 00:40.413
This is Claire Bennet,
and that was
attempt number six.

00:40.499 --> 00:42.455
It really does
break my heart.

00:44.045 --> 00:46.081
MOLLY: Please don’t.
Please don’t hurt me.

00:46.172 --> 00:47.708
Please don’t hurt me.
Please don’t hurt me.

00:47.798 --> 00:50.255
You are not
supposed to be in here.

00:51.928 --> 00:53.134
(GRUNTS)

00:54.597 --> 00:56.428
I didn't kill
these people.
Sylar did.

00:56.515 --> 00:57.595
You're under arrest.

00:57.683 --> 00:58.798
What?

00:59.310 --> 01:00.766
Hello.

01:00.853 --> 01:04.186
Nice to meet you.
I love New York!

01:15.368 --> 01:18.826
Mr. lsaac Mendez?
Hello?

01:20.164 --> 01:21.825
Mr. lsaac?

01:23.501 --> 01:25.992
Freeze! We've got
a live one here.

01:26.087 --> 01:29.671
No English, no passport,
no American money, no ID.

01:29.757 --> 01:30.963
How long ago
did he do this?

01:31.050 --> 01:32.130
Yesterday.

01:32.218 --> 01:33.298
Yesterday.

01:34.178 --> 01:35.213
October 2.

01:35.304 --> 01:40.389
October 2? No, pal.
Today, November 8.

01:40.476 --> 01:41.841
(EXPLOSION)

02:00.454 --> 02:01.910
(GASPS)

02:16.637 --> 02:18.377
(DIGGING)

02:25.604 --> 02:29.643
MOH/NDER: When evolution
selects its agents,
it does so at a cost.

02:29.734 --> 02:32.350
Makes demands
in exchange for singularity.

02:32.445 --> 02:34.902
And you may be asked
to do something
against your very nature.

02:58.846 --> 03:03.340
Suddenly, the change in
your life that should’ve been
wonderful comes as a betrayal.

03:08.939 --> 03:13.854
It may seem cruel,
but the goal is nothing
short of self-preservation.

03:14.570 --> 03:15.935
Survival.

03:25.998 --> 03:27.283
So, if our team wins,

03:27.375 --> 03:30.037
there will be
a celebratory bonfire
where I need to represent.

03:30.127 --> 03:32.459
So, it might be,
like, midnight-ish?

03:32.546 --> 03:34.047
On a school night?

03:34.131 --> 03:35.962
A celebratory
school night.

03:40.179 --> 03:41.669
So, is that
the quarterback?

03:41.764 --> 03:42.879
Who?

03:42.973 --> 03:45.464
The boy that you like
right over there?

03:45.976 --> 03:47.637
I don't like him.

03:47.728 --> 03:50.265
I mean, he's
a very nice boy, but...

03:51.273 --> 03:52.558
Yes, he's
the quarterback.

03:52.650 --> 03:56.108
If you really wanted to
make me happy,
you'd only date nerds.

03:56.195 --> 03:58.436
Well, it worked out
very well for
your mother.

03:58.531 --> 04:01.238
I love your glasses,
Mr. Bennet.

04:01.325 --> 04:03.281
Thank you, Jackie.

04:03.369 --> 04:04.779
Rumor has it
you're a local hero,

04:04.870 --> 04:06.576
pulled a man out of
a burning train car.

04:06.664 --> 04:10.373
You heard about that?
O.M.G.,
does everybody know?

04:10.459 --> 04:13.292
It was on the news.
You told half the school
to set their TiVos.

04:13.379 --> 04:16.337
It's going to be
the cornerstone of my
campaign for class president.

04:16.424 --> 04:18.210
I'm running on a platform
of moral, mental,

04:18.300 --> 04:21.087
and social advancement
through good deeds.

04:21.178 --> 04:22.714
What do you think?

04:24.014 --> 04:25.003
(MOCKS GIGGLE)

04:25.850 --> 04:28.091
I think
I need to get something
out of my locker.

04:28.185 --> 04:29.174
Hey.

04:31.814 --> 04:33.145
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

04:34.650 --> 04:36.186
Claire,

04:38.404 --> 04:40.611
be careful. Okay?

04:51.000 --> 04:53.412
(BOTH SPEAKING JAPANESE)

06:49.326 --> 06:50.441
(GRUNTS)

07:09.013 --> 07:10.674
(SLURPING)

07:12.808 --> 07:13.923
(GRUNTS)

07:23.819 --> 07:26.185
lt'll work. We'll have
the fundraiser here
and not the ballroom.

07:26.280 --> 07:27.941
It makes me look
fiscally responsible.

07:28.032 --> 07:30.444
Yes, it does.
Pete, just the man
I want to see.

07:30.576 --> 07:32.862
I need to talk to you.
What do you think?
Red or blue?

07:32.953 --> 07:34.693
I don't know,
blue?

07:35.706 --> 07:36.946
I'm going to
go red.

07:37.041 --> 07:38.121
The President
wears red.

07:38.208 --> 07:40.244
So, are you going
to come tonight?
Going to break out the suit?

07:40.336 --> 07:42.952
Have a couple of drinks.
Rebuff the advances
of my cute interns?

07:43.047 --> 07:44.162
NATHAN: Emily.

07:44.256 --> 07:45.632
Yeah, I'm going
to be there but,
listen, I...

07:45.716 --> 07:47.877
I tried it again.
Tried what?

07:47.968 --> 07:49.754
What do you mean,
"What?" What do you
think that I mean?

07:49.887 --> 07:51.923
Thank you.
I tried to fly.

07:52.514 --> 07:54.175
Would you keep
your voice down?

07:54.266 --> 07:57.224
You were there.
Last night I could fly.
This morning, nothing.

07:57.311 --> 07:58.642
I nearly broke
my neck trying.

07:58.729 --> 08:00.139
Well, that would
have solved one
of our problems.

08:00.230 --> 08:01.606
Yeah, so,
I went to the library

08:01.690 --> 08:03.351
to see if
I could find anything
on human flight.

08:03.442 --> 08:06.058
Huh, I came across
this amazing book.

08:06.737 --> 08:10.195
Listen to this,
"Genes determine obesity,
blood pressure.

08:10.282 --> 08:12.022
"Out of the
30 billion possibilities,

08:12.117 --> 08:14.494
"one might contain
the potential
for human flight."

08:14.578 --> 08:16.739
This guy knows
what's going on.

08:16.830 --> 08:17.819
Chandra Suresh.

08:17.915 --> 08:20.497
He's a genetics
professor in India.
I called.

08:21.126 --> 08:22.866
They said that
he quit six months ago.

08:22.961 --> 08:24.917
They think
he's here in New York.

08:25.005 --> 08:25.960
We've got to
find this guy.

08:26.090 --> 08:27.751
We've got a more
immediate problem here.
What?

08:28.509 --> 08:31.626
It's this woman reporter.
She's poking around into
why you jumped off the roof.

08:31.720 --> 08:33.051
Nathan, we flew.

08:33.138 --> 08:34.594
Aren't you curious
how this happened?

08:34.682 --> 08:37.845
Yeah, lwant answers
just like everyone else, man.
Just like you, okay?

08:37.935 --> 08:40.176
But right now, today,
I'm trying to find a way
to put a spin on this,

08:40.270 --> 08:42.226
so it doesn't look like
crazy runs in our family.

08:42.314 --> 08:44.430
I need to figure out
why this is happening
to me, to us.

08:44.525 --> 08:46.265
I've got responsibilities,
Pete. Okay?

08:46.360 --> 08:49.022
I've got an election to win
and a family to feed, okay?

08:49.113 --> 08:52.150
All right. So, what
do you want to
tell that reporter?

08:52.241 --> 08:55.324
I know one thing
we can't tell her,
the truth.

08:58.038 --> 08:59.949
(MOHINDER TYPING)

09:04.253 --> 09:05.914
(DOOR LOCK RATTLING)

09:06.463 --> 09:07.964
(COCMNG)

09:13.262 --> 09:15.719
Sorry, I still have
your dad's keys.

09:15.806 --> 09:17.091
(MOHINDER SIGHS)

09:17.182 --> 09:18.558
Maybe I shouldn't?

09:18.642 --> 09:19.848
Sorry.

09:20.227 --> 09:22.593
After being attacked,
every noise I hear...

09:23.480 --> 09:24.811
I'm sorry.

09:25.482 --> 09:27.894
Well, this is
macaroni and cheese.

09:28.402 --> 09:32.145
It's what Americans eat
when they want to
commit suicide slowly.

09:32.239 --> 09:34.571
Your dad said mine
was the best he ever had,

09:34.658 --> 09:36.319
but he was from India, so...

09:36.410 --> 09:38.571
Thank you.
You're very kind.

09:39.288 --> 09:42.030
You look like hell.
When was the
last time you slept?

09:43.625 --> 09:47.709
All this work. I'm no
closer to understanding
my father's research.

09:47.796 --> 09:49.707
Well, what about
the program on
your dad's computer?

09:49.798 --> 09:51.663
Didn't you say
he cracked some code?

09:51.759 --> 09:53.124
I thought he had.

09:53.510 --> 09:55.842
The algorithm,
it's gibberish.

09:56.096 --> 09:58.052
Know anybody
who speaks gibberish?

10:02.686 --> 10:06.270
The man with
the horn-rimmed glasses,
he chased me around the world.

10:06.356 --> 10:09.519
Madras, Manhattan,
this very apartment
looking for it.

10:09.610 --> 10:11.271
But this isn't anything.

10:12.196 --> 10:13.652
Well, then
why would he build it?

10:13.739 --> 10:14.819
VVhy?

10:14.907 --> 10:16.738
It was always this way
with my father.

10:16.825 --> 10:18.656
Every question met
with another question.

10:18.744 --> 10:20.780
Never an answer.
Only why.

10:21.371 --> 10:22.781
Even after he's dead.

10:23.999 --> 10:25.614
Well, what about
the map?

10:25.709 --> 10:26.824
The map.

10:26.919 --> 10:30.207
The map is nothing
until I can decipher
the principle behind it.

10:30.297 --> 10:32.128
You know, if I could find
even one such person,

10:32.216 --> 10:34.127
it would validate
everything he believed.

10:35.886 --> 10:37.296
But I can't.

10:37.387 --> 10:39.298
Your father had
a lot of faith in you.

10:40.390 --> 10:42.767
My father only cared about
proving he was right.

10:43.519 --> 10:47.011
He left his country,
his family,
chasing this insanity.

10:47.105 --> 10:50.097
And now I'm wasting
my life trying to
prove him sane.

10:50.192 --> 10:51.602
Where did it get me?

10:52.820 --> 10:54.060
Mohinderl

10:56.406 --> 10:58.818
I'm sorry,
I'm just so tired.

11:17.135 --> 11:18.261
MOHINDER: Sylar.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.551
What is it?

11:24.434 --> 11:25.765
Yet another question.

11:30.941 --> 11:31.976
(SIGHS)

11:32.067 --> 11:34.103
I don't know how else
to explain this.

11:34.778 --> 11:38.862
I heard a little girl
call for help. I went to her.
That's all that happened.

11:38.949 --> 11:40.689
So you just waltzed right in,

11:40.784 --> 11:42.695
found a kid
hiding in a wall,

11:42.786 --> 11:44.367
then pulled the name Sylar
out of your ass,

11:44.454 --> 11:45.990
when only a handful
of us know that name.

11:46.081 --> 11:51.041
(STAMMERING) It was like
someone was talking to me,

11:51.128 --> 11:52.538
except it was in my head.

11:52.629 --> 11:54.711
The voices tell you
anything else?

11:55.966 --> 11:59.208
They want you
to do things? Rob a store?
Kill the President?

11:59.303 --> 12:00.509
No.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.758
It's more like I can

12:03.849 --> 12:08.092
hear people's thoughts
or something. I don't know.

12:11.857 --> 12:13.688
Can you tell me
what I'm thinking?

12:15.152 --> 12:18.144
No, I really
can't control this.
It just sort of happens.

12:18.447 --> 12:21.063
Give it a shot, Karnack.
I'm wide open.

12:23.160 --> 12:25.993
You think
I'm nuts or stupid.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.908
Great trick.
Stop wasting my time.

12:30.083 --> 12:31.334
(SIGHING)

12:34.671 --> 12:37.287
Parkman, lneed this
more than you do.
/ need this.

12:37.382 --> 12:39.088
No one believes in me.

12:39.176 --> 12:40.712
Nobody believes in you.

12:43.764 --> 12:45.880
I know what that's like.

12:52.898 --> 12:55.105
How much longer
do I have to be in here?

12:56.151 --> 12:57.732
Depends.

12:59.863 --> 13:01.854
How would you like
to work with the FBI?

13:10.540 --> 13:11.916
ZACK: Claire.

13:12.000 --> 13:13.501
What are you doing
running off to
an away game?

13:13.585 --> 13:16.918
That tape with all
your attempts at bodily harm
is still missing.

13:17.005 --> 13:19.041
Yeah, well, if someone
finds it, we'll just
tell them you're some

13:19.132 --> 13:21.669
visual effects geek
who did it
with his computer.

13:21.760 --> 13:24.092
Now, can I get back
to my life, please?

13:24.179 --> 13:26.591
So that's it?
You're just going to
go pump your pom-poms

13:26.682 --> 13:29.139
and pretend
you're no different than
any other girl on the squad?

13:29.226 --> 13:30.341
Yes, actually.

13:30.435 --> 13:32.391
But you are, Claire.

13:32.479 --> 13:34.140
You are different.
Don't you see that?

13:34.231 --> 13:35.812
Don't you see that
none of this matters?

13:35.899 --> 13:37.890
(STAMMERING)
School spirit doesn't matter.

13:37.985 --> 13:42.979
Being a pretty blond
cheerleader doesn't matter.
It's not who you are anymore.

13:43.073 --> 13:44.529
Who am I?

13:45.409 --> 13:48.993
So what? I can crawl
through a wood chipper
and live to tell about it?

13:49.079 --> 13:50.569
That narrows
my choices in life

13:50.664 --> 13:53.371
to freak or guinea pig,
in most cases both.

13:54.626 --> 13:58.460
What's wrong with
wanting to be normal?
You should try it.

13:59.256 --> 14:01.247
(BELL RINGING)

14:11.518 --> 14:13.019
What are
you doing here?

14:13.103 --> 14:15.389
The door was open.

14:17.566 --> 14:21.525
Isaac, you have to get back
to work. Your editor...
The comic book is late.

14:21.611 --> 14:23.818
You were taking them,
weren't you?

14:23.905 --> 14:25.190
Yes, I'm going to sell them
in my gallery,

14:25.282 --> 14:28.069
and with the money
we can get you
straightened out, into rehab.

14:29.244 --> 14:32.407
I'm not going
into rehab.

14:32.497 --> 14:37.241
I found all yourjunk.
The drugs, all of it.
I flushed everything.

14:37.335 --> 14:38.495
How am I supposed
to paint the future?

14:38.587 --> 14:41.374
Nobody can paint the future.
That's the drugs talking.

14:41.465 --> 14:44.002
Look around you
at all of these paintings.

14:44.092 --> 14:45.878
Every one of them
has come true.

14:45.969 --> 14:47.175
(EXCLAIMS)

14:47.637 --> 14:51.471
And does that include
this big one on the floor
of New York going nuclear?

14:51.558 --> 14:52.798
Yes.

14:54.311 --> 14:56.802
I don't know how,
I don't know when,

14:58.565 --> 15:00.601
but I have to stop it.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.528
I don't want to
lose you, Simone.

15:09.701 --> 15:13.319
But if you don't
believe in me,
then you shouldn't be here.

15:20.170 --> 15:21.580
Fine.

15:22.047 --> 15:23.833
You think you can
paint the future?

15:25.300 --> 15:27.006
Paint one
without me in it.

15:29.429 --> 15:31.545
(PHONE RINGING)

15:36.520 --> 15:37.509
Hello?

15:37.604 --> 15:39.640
(H/RO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

15:39.731 --> 15:42.473
I can't understand
a word you're saying.

15:42.567 --> 15:44.603
Stop calling me here.
You've got the wrong number.

15:44.694 --> 15:46.070
Wrong number.

15:46.905 --> 15:48.441
(CRASHING)

15:50.534 --> 15:53.367
(BOTH SPEAKING JAPANESE)

16:36.371 --> 16:38.077
(APOLOGIZES IN JAPANESE)

16:52.345 --> 16:53.846
(SHOUTING IN JAPANESE)

16:58.810 --> 17:00.095
(TIRES SCREECHING)

17:00.187 --> 17:01.427
(SHOUTING IN JAPANESE)

17:02.439 --> 17:03.428
(GASPING)

17:05.442 --> 17:06.682
(ENGINE STOPPING)

17:29.132 --> 17:30.588
(SHOUTING IN JAPANESE)

17:34.846 --> 17:36.802
(BOTH SPEAKING JAPANESE)

17:49.486 --> 17:50.475
(GRUNTING)

17:59.663 --> 18:01.574
(PANTING)

18:24.771 --> 18:26.557
Hi.
Hi.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.518
How'd you sleep?
Good.

18:30.068 --> 18:31.604
Where are we?

18:35.156 --> 18:37.488
On our way to
grandma's house.

18:50.213 --> 18:51.828
Micah!

18:52.382 --> 18:53.792
Grandma!

18:53.883 --> 18:56.670
Oh, my,
you've grown.

18:56.761 --> 18:57.921
You always say that.

18:58.013 --> 18:59.469
I do.
Yes, you do.

18:59.556 --> 19:02.593
Hmm. Why don't
you go on inside?

19:05.520 --> 19:07.056
You look thin.

19:09.024 --> 19:11.606
Look, I know what
it's like to raise
a boy on your own,

19:11.693 --> 19:15.561
to be stretched so far
you wish you could be in
two places at once. I get it.

19:16.573 --> 19:19.189
But that boy needs more
than you've been giving him.

19:19.284 --> 19:22.902
He needs a steady hand
and a stable environment.
I can give him that.

19:22.996 --> 19:25.612
Why? Because D.L.
grew up to be
such a model citizen?

19:27.667 --> 19:30.500
My son, your husband,

19:30.587 --> 19:32.077
is a good man.

19:35.008 --> 19:38.250
Recognize this?
I found it in the desert.

19:38.887 --> 19:40.548
What's that
supposed to be?

19:41.765 --> 19:44.256
This belonged to
one of the men that
your son murdered.

19:45.310 --> 19:47.221
I took it
out of a grave.

19:47.312 --> 19:49.849
You know that all of
D.L.'s crew wore these.

19:49.939 --> 19:52.897
D.L. wouldn't murder
anybody.

19:53.860 --> 19:55.066
Even
Wrong.

19:55.153 --> 19:58.941
He robbed Linderman and got
away with two million dollars,
and then he killed his crew.

19:59.032 --> 20:05.278
My son was framed, and
he'd be rotting in some prison
if he hadn't escaped.

20:05.372 --> 20:08.990
Besides, if D.L. had
two million dollars,

20:09.084 --> 20:13.043
honey, he'd be on some
tropical island some place
sitting out his years

20:13.129 --> 20:14.539
with Micah.

20:17.300 --> 20:19.416
I want you out
of my son's life.

20:19.511 --> 20:21.627
Yeah, well, people
in hell want ice water.

20:21.721 --> 20:23.382
It doesn't mean
they're going to get it.

20:23.473 --> 20:27.011
Paulette, you have no idea
what I am capable of.

20:38.530 --> 20:39.815
MATT: Do you want to tell me
why I'm still here,

20:39.906 --> 20:41.066
or am I just gonna
follow you around?

20:41.157 --> 20:43.239
AUDREY:
I need you to talk to her.
Find out what she knows.

20:43.326 --> 20:44.281
Talk to who?

20:44.369 --> 20:46.701
Molly Walker,
the little girl
you found.

20:46.788 --> 20:48.028
We're keeping her here
where it's safe

20:48.123 --> 20:49.738
till we can figure out
what to do with her.

20:49.833 --> 20:52.825
She's been through severe
trauma, both parents murdered
right in front of her.

20:52.919 --> 20:54.250
She hasn't said a word
since we brought her here.

20:54.337 --> 20:55.622
What makes you think
she's going to talk to me?

20:55.713 --> 20:58.455
Well, if you're really
a mind-reader
she won't need to.

20:58.967 --> 21:01.299
Who is this Sylar?
What's he doing?

21:01.845 --> 21:04.177
I pieced a trail across
a dozen states,

21:04.264 --> 21:07.222
all people impaled by
household objects,
bones broken,

21:07.308 --> 21:09.970
all without any traceable
sign of physical contact.

21:10.061 --> 21:12.552
But only some of them
involve any mutilation
of the head or neck,

21:12.647 --> 21:14.262
so they don't see
the connections.

21:14.357 --> 21:16.564
But you think
it's all him.

21:16.651 --> 21:19.358
I think it's going to get
a lot worse if someone
doesn't go after him.

21:20.488 --> 21:22.399
MOHINDER: Mr. Sylar? Hello?

21:22.740 --> 21:24.071
(EDEN SHUSHING)

21:26.619 --> 21:29.235
What are you
actually gonna do
if Sylar's in there?

21:29.330 --> 21:31.821
If Sylar killed my father,
I need to know why.

